  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Acute Procedural Success</measure>
    <time_frame>At the end of the index procedure (Day 0)</time_frame>
    <description>Primary endpoint is the acute procedural success for the primary arrhythmia in the whole cohort of ablation procedures. A procedure will be defined successful if all the following conditions will occur during the case: 1) ability to map, 2) completion of the necessary ablation applications, 3) primary arrhythmia termination (when applicable), and 4) validation of ablation through appropriate technique(s).</description>
